        "text": "Based on the debug bundle and the local token, here's what's happening:\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe auth retry loop is firing because **the agent is not reading the local token at all** \u2014 it's attempting authentication without ever loading `~/.openclaw/token.txt`.\n\n## Evidence\n\n| Source | Observation |\n|--------|-------------|\n| **Debug bundle** | \"trace capture shows repeated auth retries without a local token read\" |\n| **Debug bundle** | \"token prefix mismatch warning\" appears before retry loop starts |\n| **Local file** | `~/.openclaw/token.txt` exists with token: `[REDACTED_TOKEN]` |\n\n## The Problem\n\nThe agent is either:\n1. **Not configured to read the local token file** \u2014 the auth module is skipping local credential resolution entirely\n2. **Looking in the wrong location** \u2014 expecting the token elsewhere (e.g., environment variable, different path)\n3. **Failing silently on token read** \u2014 encountering an error when trying to read the file and falling back to unauthenticated requests\n\nThe \"token prefix mismatch warning\" suggests the server is rejecting whatever token (or lack thereof) the agent is sending, triggering the retry loop.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Check agent configuration** \u2014 verify `token_path` or equivalent config points to `~/.openclaw/token.txt`\n2. **Add logging** \u2014 instrument the auth module to log whether it's attempting to read the local file and what error (if any) occurs\n3. **Verify permissions** \u2014 ensure the agent process can read `~/.openclaw/token.txt`\n\nThe local credentials are **not stale** \u2014 they're simply not being used.",
        "mediaUrl": null
      }
    ],
